<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n36208d"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n36" href="#n36208d">N36 (VI.B.29)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n36all.htm#n36208d"> 208(d)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> Abluted ~</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources"><font color="green">[Mormonism.]</font> So far as I have been able to determine, the Saints still wear their long, peculiar drawers as part of their faith. Wife No. 19 <font color="green">[apostate wife of Bringham Young who wrote a book under this title]</font> was promised that she should be a celestial queen and should receive the Endowments of the order. She tells of having been led to the bathroom. where she was <mark>abluted</mark> and then anointed head to foot with olive oil. <small> Charles W. Ferguson, <a name="CFCT" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#CFCT"><cite title="source">The Confusion of Tongues</cite></a> (1928; rpt. May 1929) 391</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
